            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This still happens on master 48e6147e64b819d2a4130697bb348dcd368a4391\n\n(Unlike the original post this is in Wezterm + WSL)\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c4801ef-f0ca-4a1b-9adc-b6a85534024c\n\nThat said resizing in general can get funky. It's hard for me to know if Neovim is reflowing properly and the terminal is broken underneath in some way or what.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0a2c4ae8-2446-489b-b0e7-bd48f5812614\n\nEdit: It happens even with a parent bash that ran with `bash --noprofile --norc` + `:terminal bash --noprofile --norc`. So I can at least rule out any bash-ism or personal configuration.",
